<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="75" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Salvador</gloss>
                                to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-24"><hi rend="italic">April 24,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Ministers of Nicaragua and of this Republic advised me last night that
                            peace on terms honorable to both Republics was signed. In the name of
                            the people and my own I tender to you the testimonials of thanks for the
                            good offices lent in the cause of peace.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">F. Figueroa.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>